            h1 Typography

          h2#headings Headings
          p All HTML headings, <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> through <code>&lt;h6&gt;</code> are available.
          
          .bs-docs-example
            h1 h1. Heading 1
            h2 h2. Heading 2
            h3 h3. Heading 3
            h4 h4. Heading 4
            h5 h5. Heading 5
            h6 h6. Heading 6
          

          h2#body-copyBody copy
          p Bootstrap's global default <code>font-size</code> is <strong>14px</strong>, with a <code>line-height</code> of <strong>20px</strong>. This is applied to the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> and all paragraphs. In addition, <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> (paragraphs) receive a bottom margin of half their line-height (9px by default).

          .bs-docs-example
            p Nullam quis risus eget urna mollis ornare vel eu leo. Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Nullam id dolor id nibh ultricies vehicula.
            p Cum sociis natoque penatibus et magnis dis parturient montes, nascetur ridiculus mus. Donec ullamcorper nulla non metus auctor fringilla. Duis mollis, est non commodo luctus, nisi erat porttitor ligula, eget lacinia odio sem nec elit. Donec ullamcorper nulla non metus auctor fringilla.
            p Maecenas sed diam eget risus varius blandit sit amet non magna. Donec id elit non mi porta gravida at eget metus. Duis mollis, est non commodo luctus, nisi erat porttitor ligula, eget lacinia odio sem nec elit.
          
          pre.prettyprint">&lt;p&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;

          h3 Lead body copy
          p Make a paragraph stand out by adding <code>.lead</code>.
          .bs-docs-example
            p.leadVivamus sagittis lacus vel augue laoreet rutrum faucibus dolor auctor. Duis mollis, est non commodo luctus.
          
          pre.prettyprint &lt;p class="lead"&gt;...&lt;/p&gt;

          h3 Built with Less
          p The typographic scale is based on two LESS variables in <strong>variables.less</strong>: <code>@baseFontSize</code> and <code>@baseLineHeight</code>. The first is the base font-size used throughout and the second is the base line-height. We use those variables and some simple math to create the margins, paddings, and line-heights of all our type and more. Customize them and Bootstrap adapts.


          hr.bs-docs-separator


          h2#emphasis Emphasis
          p Make use of HTML's default emphasis tags with lightweight styles.

          h3 <code>&lt;small&gt;</code>
          p For de-emphasizing inline or blocks of text, <small>use the small tag.</small>
          .bs-docs-example
            p <small>This line of text is meant to be treated as fine print.</small>
          

          h3 <code>&lt;strong&gt;</code>
          p For emphasizing a snippet of text with <strong>important</strong>
          .bs-docs-example
            The following snippet of text is <strong>rendered as bold text</strong>.
          
          pre.prettyprint &lt;strong&gt;rendered as bold text&lt;/strong&gt;

          h3 <code>&lt;em&gt;</code>
          p For emphasizing a snippet of text with <em>stress</em>
          .bs-docs-example
            p The following snippet of text is <em>rendered as italicized text</em>.
          
          pre.prettyprint &lt;em&gt;rendered as italicized text&lt;/em&gt;

          p span.label.label-info Heads up! 
          | Feel free to use <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> in HTML5. <code>&lt;b&gt;</code> is meant to highlight words or phrases without conveying additional importance while <code>&lt;i&gt;</code> is mostly for voice, technical terms, etc.


          hr.bs-docs-separator

          h2#abbreviations Abbreviations
          p Stylized implemenation of HTML's <code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code> element for abbreviations and acronyms to show the expanded version on hover. Abbreviations with a <code>title</code> attribute have a light dotted bottom border and a help cursor on hover, providing additional context on hover.

          h3 <code>&lt;abbr&gt;</code>
          p For expanded text on long hover of an abbreviation, include the <code>title</code> attribute.
          .bs-docs-example
            p An abbreviation of the word attribute is <abbr title="attribute">attr</abbr>.
          
          pre.prettyprint &lt;abbr title="attribute"&gt;attr&lt;/abbr&gt;

          h3 <code>&lt;abbr class="initialism"&gt;</code>
          p Add <code>.initialism</code> to an abbreviation for a slightly smaller font-size.
          .bs-docs-example
            p <abbr title="HyperText Markup Language" class="initialism">HTML</abbr> is the best thing since sliced bread.
         
          pre.prettyprint &lt;abbr title="attribute" class="initialism"&gt;attr&lt;/abbr&gt;


